The White House Office of Science and Technology Policy director, John P. Holdren, released a statement endorsing the candidacy of Stanford University Professor Dr. Christopher Field for the position of Chair of the Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change (IPCC). Holdren highlights Dr. Field's qualifications, including his pioneering research in climate-related fields, leadership roles in academic institutions, and contributions to major IPCC reports. Holdren also emphasizes Dr. Field's commitment to scientific integrity and his ability to facilitate cooperation and consensus among diverse scientific perspectives. Holdren hopes that Dr. Field will be selected for this crucial role.